To calculate the Net Profit Margin, we use the following formula:

\[ \text{Net Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{\text{Net Profit}}{\text{Total Revenue}} \right) \times 100 \]

Given the data:
- Net Profit = -2,035,736.52
- Total Revenue = 6,836,701.10

Now, plug in the values:

\[ \text{Net Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{-2,035,736.52}{6,836,701.10} \right) \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Net Profit Margin} = (-0.2977) \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Net Profit Margin} = -29.77\% \]

So, the solution is:

```json
{"solution": {'Net Profit Margin': '-29.77%'} }
```
